## STEP 4 — SPACING SYSTEM

The project uses **ad-hoc spacing** — no centralized spacing scale.  
Most common values observed:

| Value | Usage |
|---|---|
| `4px` | Small gaps, margin tweaks |
| `6px` | Badge padding, small gaps |
| `8px` | Action gaps, icon spacing |
| `10px` | Badge padding |
| `12px` | Cell padding, modal gaps |
| `14px` | Nav padding, search padding |
| `16px` | Standard gap (nav, filter rows) |
| `20px` | Section spacing |
| `24px` | Card padding, modal padding |
| `28px` | Modal footer margin |
| `32px` | Page content padding |
| `40px` | Empty state, modal top padding |
| `48px` | Login card padding, feature list |
| `60px` | Sign-in panel padding |

Fluent UI tokens (`spacingVerticalL`, etc.) are used in `NavRail.tsx` and `AppLayout.tsx`, but all feature pages use raw pixel values.

