## STEP 6 — HARDCODED STYLE VIOLATIONS

> [!CAUTION]
> The following are hardcoded color values that **bypass the CSS variable token system** — making system-wide theming impossible without find-and-replace.

### Critical Conflicts — Two Parallel Palettes

The most serious issue: **two completely different "blue" primaries coexist**:

| Palette | Blue Value | Used In |
|---|---|---|
| **Enterprise palette** (original) | `#193e6b` (Midnight) | TopBar, NavRail, UserEnrichment, UserRoleAssign, Modal CSS, `colors.css` token |
| **Audit palette** (new spec) | `#2F4A73` (Medium Blue) | AuditLogViewerPage tabs/headers/timestamps |

These are **visually different colors** that appear on the same page. This is a design inconsistency.

Similarly for text:

| Old Components | New Audit Component |
|---|---|
| `#333333` (primary text) | `#1F2D3D` (primary text) |
| `#666666` (secondary text) | `#6B7785` (secondary text) |
| `#6B7280` (token muted) | `#6B7785` (hardcoded muted) |

### File-by-file hardcoded colors

| File | Hardcoded Values |
|---|---|
| `AuditLogViewerPage.tsx` | 19 distinct hex values, all hardcoded in Griffel |
| `topbar-vanilla.css` | `#193e6b`, `#B3A125`, `#dc3545`, `#333`, `#777`, `#666` |
| `UserEnrichmentPage.tsx` | `#193e6b`, `#666666`, `#333333`, `#28a745`, `#dc3545`, `#007bff` |
| `UserRoleAssignmentPage.tsx` | `#193e6b`, `#666666` |
| `AssignmentTable.tsx` | `#193e6b`, `#333333`, `#666666`, `#999999`, `#FFFFFF` |
| `AssignmentFilters.tsx` | `#666666`, `#333333`, `#193e6b`, `#28a745`, `#999999` |
| `RoleBadge.tsx` | `#dc3545`, `#28a745`, `#d39e00`, `#007bff`, `#6c757d` |
| `StatusBadge.tsx` (user-role-assign) | `#28a745`, `#dc3545` |
| `AddSecurityRoleModal.module.css` | `#6b7280`, `#1f2937`, `#dc2626`, `#d1d5db`, `#f3f4f6` |

